D. Document Processing Service
This handles all document-related operations.
What it does
uploads files
reads PDF or DOCX
extracts text
chunks text into smaller parts
creates embeddings
stores embeddings in vector database
supports semantic search
Why chunking is needed
AI models cannot always process large files directly.

So document text is split into smaller sections called chunks.
Example:
A 20-page company policy document becomes many smaller paragraphs.

These chunks are converted into embeddings and saved.
What are embeddings
Embeddings are numerical representations of text.

They help the system find meaning-based matches instead of exact keyword matches.
Example
User asks:
What is the refund policy?
The system does not search only the word “refund.”

It searches semantically and finds the most relevant section.
Tools
Apache PDFBox or Tika for file parsing
LangChain4j for embedding and retrieval
Vector DB like Qdrant / Weaviate / Pinecone
E. Notification Service
This sends alerts and updates.
What it does
sends email notifications
sends Slack messages
gives system alerts in dashboard
informs users when a task is created or a report is ready
Example
If AI extracts a task from an email, the Notification Service sends:
New Task Created: Complete sales report by Friday
Why it matters
Automation is incomplete unless users are informed.
Tools
JavaMailSender for emails
Slack webhook API
WebSocket or frontend notifications
7. Core features explained in detail
A. Document Intelligence
This feature allows users to upload business documents and ask questions.
Example
Upload:
HR policy PDF
company handbook
project report
SOP document
Ask:
What is the leave policy?
What is the refund rule?
What is the escalation process?
How it works
User uploads file
Document service extracts text
Text is chunked
Embeddings are created
Embeddings stored in vector DB
User question is embedded
Relevant chunks are retrieved
LLM generates final answer from those chunks
This is called RAG — Retrieval Augmented Generation.
B. AI Chat Assistant
This gives a chatbot-like interface for employees.
What users can ask
