9. Messaging system
Use Kafka or RabbitMQ to connect services asynchronously.
Why messaging is needed
In microservices, one service should not always directly wait for another.
Example:
Email Service receives email
publishes event
Task Extraction Service consumes event
Notification Service consumes result
This makes the platform scalable and professional.
Example event flow
new_email_received
task_extracted
report_generated
notification_ready
RabbitMQ is simpler. Kafka is stronger for large real-time systems.
